</line><line>Vigilante (Treddon):
...Let me ask you guys a question. Have you noticed... that there are two kinds of people in this world?
</line><line>Phoenix:
...Huh?
</line><line>Vigilante (Treddon):
There are those who <textEffects>sit</textEffects> and those who get <textEffects>sat on</textEffects>.
</line><line>Phoenix:
Wh-whatever you say...
</line><line>Vigilante (Treddon):
So? What do you say? Wanna try seeing the world from a whole new perspective?
</line><line>Layton:
............ It would seem Miss Foxy, too, is enjoying the world from a much higher perspective. I must say, it is quite fascinating.
</line><line>Vigilante (Foxy):
Mmm, I'm so glad you noticed. By the way, you know what? They won't just let anyone into the contest. There ARE try-outs.
</line><line>Luke:
Did you say there are try-outs...?
</line><line>Layton:
Miss Foxy, do you perhaps mean...
</line><line>Vigilante (Foxy):
You got it. The try-outs are <textEffects>puzzle</textEffects> try-outs.
</line><line>Layton:
...! If that is indeed the case... then allow me to throw my hat into the ring. Figuratively speaking, of course.
